Ichthydium contains an additional four species that carry scales or spines in the posterior trunk region I. crassum , I. diacanthum , I. dubium and I. squamigerum . I. crassum , I. diacanthum and I. dubium have spines but apparently lack scales which together with the different shape of the furca, differentiate them from I . skandicum n. sp. (
Daday, 1905 ;
Schwank, 1990 ;
Balsamo & Todaro, 1995 ). I. squamigerum has two pairs of keeled scales at the base of the furca compared to four pairs in I. skandicum n. sp. Moreover, at least another noticeable trait distinguishes these two species, that is the furca which is long ( 28–30 µm) and tong-shaped in I. skandicum n. sp. and short ( 13–18 µm) and straight in I. squamigerum (see
Balsamo & Fregni, 1995 ).

Localities: Bog close to E 14 , Jämtland, Sweden ( 63 º 21.248 ’N
; 12 º 35.403 ’E
).

Localities: Trösvattnet, Västmanland, Sweden ( 59 º 33.211 ’N
